TITLE: Defining a Basic Kotlin Data Class
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the fundamental syntax for declaring a data class in Kotlin. The `data` keyword before `class` instructs the compiler to automatically generate standard methods like `equals()`, `hashCode()`, `toString()`, `componentN()` functions for destructuring, and a `copy()` function based on the properties declared in the primary constructor (`name` and `age`).
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/data-classes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
data class User(val name: String, val age: Int)
```

