TITLE: Try-Catch Expression in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use a `try-catch` block as an expression in Kotlin. The `try-catch` expression returns the value of the last expression in the `try` block or the `catch` block if an exception is caught.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/idioms.md#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun test() {
    val result = try {
        count()
    } catch (e: ArithmeticException) {
        throw IllegalStateException(e)
    }

    // Working with result
}
```

