TITLE: Exposing Kotlin Property as Public Field in Java with @JvmField
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to annotate a Kotlin property (`ID`) within a class (`User`) with `@JvmField`. This exposes the property directly as a public field in the generated Java class, allowing direct access (`user.ID`) from Java code instead of using getter methods. The property must have a backing field, not be private, and meet other specific criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/jvm/java-to-kotlin-interop.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
