TITLE: Referencing Java Synthetic Properties
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create references to Java synthetic properties in Kotlin, starting from Kotlin 1.8.20. It uses the `Person` class defined in Java and demonstrates sorting a list of `Person` objects by age using a property reference.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/jvm/java-interop.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
val persons = listOf(Person("Jack", 11), Person("Sofie", 12), Person("Peter", 11))
    persons
         // Call a reference to Java synthetic property:
        .sortedBy(Person::age)
         // Call Java getter via the Kotlin property syntax:
        .forEach { person -> println(person.name) }
```

