TITLE: Declaring a Singleton Object in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to declare a singleton object using the `object` keyword in Kotlin. This example shows a `DataProviderManager` object that manages a list of data providers, demonstrating the basic structure and functionality of object declarations. It includes registration and retrieval of data providers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/object-declarations.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
// Declares a Singleton object to manage data providers
object DataProviderManager {
    private val providers = mutableListOf<DataProvider>()

    // Registers a new data provider
    fun registerDataProvider(provider: DataProvider) {
        providers.add(provider)
    }

    // Retrieves all registered data providers
    val allDataProviders: Collection<DataProvider> 
        get() = providers
}

// Example data provider interface
interface DataProvider {
    fun provideData(): String
}

// Example data provider implementation
class ExampleDataProvider : DataProvider {
    override fun provideData(): String {
        return "Example data"
    }
}

fun main() {
    // Creates an instance of ExampleDataProvider
