TITLE: Configuring Kotlin JVM compilation options (Groovy DSL)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures Kotlin compiler options for the 'main' compilation of the JVM target using the Groovy DSL.  It uses the `compilations.main` syntax to access the compilation and configure its `compilerOptions`, setting the JVM target to Java 1.8. It also demonstrates how to access the compilation output and runtime dependencies. Requires Gradle Groovy DSL.
