TITLE: Defining a Generic Extension Function in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates defining a generic extension function `swap` applicable to `MutableList<T>` for any type `T`. The generic type parameter `T` is declared before the function name, making it usable in the receiver type expression.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/extensions.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun <T> MutableList<T>.swap(index1: Int, index2: Int) {
    val tmp = this[index1] // 'this' corresponds to the list
    this[index1] = this[index2]
    this[index2] = tmp
}
```

