TITLE: Implementing Comparable Interface for Custom Ordering in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a custom class (Version) that implements the Comparable interface to define a natural order for comparison of version numbers with major and minor components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/collection-ordering.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class Version(val major: Int, val minor: Int): Comparable<Version> {
    override fun compareTo(other: Version): Int = when {
        this.major != other.major -> this.major compareTo other.major // compareTo() in the infix form 
        this.minor != other.minor -> this.minor compareTo other.minor
        else -> 0
    }
}

fun main() {    
    println(Version(1, 2) > Version(1, 3))
    println(Version(2, 0) > Version(1, 5))
}
```

