TITLE: Deep Recursive Function Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement deep recursive functions using DeepRecursiveFunction to handle deep recursion without stack overflow.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/whatsnew/whatsnew17.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class Tree(val left: Tree?, val right: Tree?)

val calculateDepth = DeepRecursiveFunction<Tree?, Int> { t ->
    if (t == null) 0 else maxOf(
        callRecursive(t.left),
        callRecursive(t.right)
    ) + 1
}

fun main() {
    val deepTree = generateSequence(Tree(null, null)) { prev ->
        Tree(prev, null)
    }.take(100_000).last()

    println(calculateDepth(deepTree)) // 100000
}
```

