TITLE: Interoperability Between Kotlin and Java Atomic Types
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the new .asJavaAtomic() and .asKotlinAtomic() extension functions to convert between Kotlin's atomic types and Java's java.util.concurrent.atomic types. This enables seamless interoperability in projects using both Kotlin and Java concurrency primitives.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/whatsnew/whatsnew2120.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
// Imports the necessary libraries
import kotlin.concurrent.atomics.*
import java.util.concurrent.atomic.*

@OptIn(ExperimentalAtomicApi::class)
fun main() {
    // Converts Kotlin AtomicInt to Java's AtomicInteger
    val kotlinAtomic = AtomicInt(42)
    val javaAtomic: AtomicInteger = kotlinAtomic.asJavaAtomic()
    println("Java atomic value: ${javaAtomic.get()}")
    // Java atomic value: 42

    // Converts Java's AtomicInteger back to Kotlin's AtomicInt
    val kotlinAgain: AtomicInt = javaAtomic.asKotlinAtomic()
    println("Kotlin atomic value: ${kotlinAgain.load()}")
    // Kotlin atomic value: 42
}
```

