TITLE: Defining an Array Copy Function with Invariant Types in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Defines a function `copy` intended to copy elements from one array (`from`) to another (`to`). It initially requires both arrays to be specifically `Array<Any>`, which limits its usability due to Kotlin's generic invariance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/generics.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun copy(from: Array<Any>, to: Array<Any>) {
    assert(from.size == to.size)
    for (i in from.indices)
        to[i] = from[i]
}
```

