TITLE: Checking if a Number is Outside a Range using !in Operator in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates using the `!in` operator to check if a value is outside a specified range. It checks if `-1` is outside the valid index range of a list (`0..list.lastIndex`) and if the list's size is outside its `indices` range.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/basic-syntax.md#2025-04-22_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun main() {
//sampleStart
    val list = listOf("a", "b", "c")

    if (-1 !in 0..list.lastIndex) {
        println("-1 is out of range")
    }
    if (list.size !in list.indices) {
        println("list size is out of valid list indices range, too")
    }
//sampleEnd
}
```

