TITLE: Implementing Multi-Criteria Sorting in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to sort a collection using multiple criteria - first by string length, and then alphabetically when lengths are equal.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/collection-ordering.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun main() {
    val sortedStrings = listOf("aaa", "bb", "c", "b", "a", "aa", "ccc")
        .sortedWith { a, b -> 
           when (val compareLengths = a.length.compareTo(b.length)) {
             0 -> a.compareTo(b)
             else -> compareLengths
           }
         }

    println(sortedStrings)
    // [a, b, c, aa, bb, aaa, ccc]
}
```

