TITLE: Finding the Longest Message Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This Kotlin code finds the `Message` object with the longest text in a list of messages. It uses the `reduce()` function, which iteratively compares two messages and returns the one with the longer text.  The `reduce()` function applies the given operation to the collection elements sequentially and returns the accumulated result. In this case, it will reduce the collection to a single `Message` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/jvm/jvm-spring-boot-collections.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
@GetMapping("findTheLongestMessage")
fun reduce(): Message {
    val messages = service.findMessages()
    return messages.reduce { first, second ->
        if (first.text.length > second.text.length) first else second
    }
}
```

