TITLE: Pinning Kotlin Objects with usePinned
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to pin a Kotlin ByteArray in memory using usePinned so its address remains stable while passing it to C functions. Pinning ensures the object won't be moved by the garbage collector.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/native/native-c-interop.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
import kotlinx.cinterop.*
import platform.posix.*

@OptIn(ExperimentalForeignApi::class)
fun readData(fd: Int) {
    val buffer = ByteArray(1024)
    buffer.usePinned { pinned ->
        while (true) {
            val length = recv(fd, pinned.addressOf(0), buffer.size.convert(), 0).toInt()
            if (length <= 0) {
                break
            }
            // Now `buffer` has raw data obtained from the `recv()` call.
        }
    }
}
```

