TITLE: Finding a Parent Node Using Reflection in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Implements a generic extension for traversing a tree and finding a parent node of a specified type using reflection. Accepts a 'Class<T>' parameter and returns the first matching ancestor or null, using 'isInstance' for runtime type checking. Suppresses unchecked cast warning as type safety is ensured by the logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/inline-functions.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun <T> TreeNode.findParentOfType(clazz: Class<T>): T? {
    var p = parent
    while (p != null && !clazz.isInstance(p)) {
        p = p.parent
    }
    @Suppress("UNCHECKED_CAST")
    return p as T?
}
```

