TITLE: Collecting Suppressed Annotation Names in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This function collects names from 'Suppress' annotations within a Kotlin file by filtering the annotations by type and extracting the arguments as a sequence of strings. It specifically looks for 'Suppress' annotations qualified as 'kotlin.Suppress'. No additional dependencies are required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/ksp/ksp-examples.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Kotlin
CODE:
```
// @file:kotlin.Suppress("Example1", "Example2")
fun KSFile.suppressedNames(): Sequence<String> = annotations
    .filter {
        it.shortName.asString() == "Suppress" &&
        it.annotationType.resolve().declaration.qualifiedName?.asString() == "kotlin.Suppress"
    }.flatMap {
        it.arguments.flatMap {
            (it.value as Array<String>).toList()
        }
    }
```

