TITLE: Finding Actual Types of Type Aliases in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Finds the actual class or interface declaration that a given type alias points to. It resolves the type of the alias, recursively resolving if it points to another type alias, until it reaches an actual class or interface. No additional dependencies are required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/ksp/ksp-examples.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Kotlin
CODE:
```
fun KSTypeAlias.findActualType(): KSClassDeclaration {
    val resolvedType = this.type.resolve().declaration
    return if (resolvedType is KSTypeAlias) {
        resolvedType.findActualType()
    } else {
        resolvedType as KSClassDeclaration
    }
}
```

