TITLE: Using Basic Reflection Features in Kotlin/JS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates obtaining class names (`simpleName`, `js.name`), checking instance types (`isInstance`), casting (`cast`), and accessing reified type arguments (`typeof()`) using the supported reflection capabilities in Kotlin/JS. It defines base and derived classes (`Shape`, `Rectangle`) and uses reflection functions within the `main` method and a helper generic function.
