TITLE: Solving Reachable Numbers with HashSet and readLine()!! in Earlier Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Presents the main solution for the "Reachable Numbers" problem tailored for Kotlin versions prior to 1.6.0. It reads the input integer using `readLine()!!.toInt()`, utilizing the not-null assertion operator `!!` because `readLine()` returns a nullable `String?`. It employs a `HashSet` to track reached numbers while iteratively applying the `f` function (defined elsewhere) and prints the size of the set upon completion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/competitive-programming.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun main() {
    var n = readLine()!!.toInt() // read integer from the input
    val reached = HashSet<Int>() // a mutable hash set 
    while (reached.add(n)) n = f(n) // iterate function f
    println(reached.size) // print answer to the output
}
```

