TITLE: Try-Finally without Catch in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates using a `try-finally` block without a `catch` block for resource cleanup. The `MockResource` simulates a resource, and the `finally` block ensures it's always closed, even if an exception occurs within the `try` block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/exceptions.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class MockResource { 
    fun use() { 
        println("Resource being used") 
        // Simulate a resource being used 
        // This throws an ArithmeticException if division by zero occurs
        val result = 100 / 0

        // This line is not executed if an exception is thrown
        println("Result: $result") 
    }

    fun close() { 
        println("Resource closed") 
    }
}

fun main() { 
    val resource = MockResource()
//sampleStart 
    try {

        // Attempts to use the resource 
        resource.use()

    } finally {

        // Ensures that the resource is always closed, even if an exception occurs 
        resource.close()
    }

    // This line is not printed if an exception is thrown
    println("End of the program")
//sampleEnd
}
```

