TITLE: Declaring Kotlin Extensions as Class Members
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates declaring an extension function (`printConnectionString` for `Host`) inside another class (`Connection`). Inside this member extension, members of both the dispatch receiver (`Connection`, accessed via `printPort()`) and the extension receiver (`Host`, accessed via `printHostname()`) can be called implicitly. The extension is callable only within the scope of the enclosing class.
