TITLE: Taking and Dropping Elements Conditionally in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use `takeWhile()`, `takeLastWhile()`, `dropWhile()`, and `dropLastWhile()` extension functions with predicates on a `List<String>`. `takeWhile` takes elements from the start as long as the predicate is true. `takeLastWhile` takes elements from the end as long as the predicate is true. `dropWhile` removes elements from the start while the predicate is true, returning the rest. `dropLastWhile` removes elements from the end while the predicate is true, returning the rest.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/collection-parts.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun main() {
//sampleStart
    val numbers = listOf("one", "two", "three", "four", "five", "six")
    println(numbers.takeWhile { !it.startsWith('f') })
    println(numbers.takeLastWhile { it != "three" })
    println(numbers.dropWhile { it.length == 3 })
    println(numbers.dropLastWhile { it.contains('i') })
//sampleEnd
}
```

