TITLE: Using Delegation with Kotlin Inline Classes
DESCRIPTION: Shows that an inline class can implement an interface by delegating the implementation to its underlying value, provided the underlying value also implements that interface. The `MyInterfaceWrapper` inline class wraps a `MyInterface` instance and delegates the interface calls to it using the `by` keyword.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/inline-classes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
interface MyInterface {
    fun bar()
    fun foo() = "foo"
}

@JvmInline
value class MyInterfaceWrapper(val myInterface: MyInterface) : MyInterface by myInterface

fun main() {
    val my = MyInterfaceWrapper(object : MyInterface {
        override fun bar() {
            // body
        }
    })
    println(my.foo()) // prints "foo"
}
```

