TITLE: Kotlin/Wasm Example in Kotlin Playground
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates a simple Kotlin/Wasm program that calculates the Ackermann function and measures its execution time. It imports the necessary libraries for time measurement and defines the `main` function to print a greeting and compute the Ackermann function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/whatsnew/whatsnew19.md#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
import kotlin.time.*\nimport kotlin.time.measureTime\n
fun main() {
    println("Hello from Kotlin/Wasm!")
    computeAck(3, 10)
}

tailrec fun ack(m: Int, n: Int): Int = when {
    m == 0 -> n + 1
    n == 0 -> ack(m - 1, 1)
    else -> ack(m - 1, ack(m, n - 1))
}

fun computeAck(m: Int, n: Int) {
    var res = 0
    val t = measureTime {
        res = ack(m, n)
    }
    println()
