TITLE: When Expression (Boolean Subject) Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This Kotlin code uses a 'when' expression with `trafficLightState` as the subject.  It assigns a corresponding traffic action based on the state (Green, Yellow, Red) and prints the resulting action to the console. Requires Kotlin 1.3 or higher.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/tour/kotlin-tour-control-flow.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
fun main() {
    val trafficLightState = "Red" // This can be "Green", "Yellow", or "Red"

    val trafficAction = when (trafficLightState) {
        "Green" -> "Go"
        "Yellow" -> "Slow down"
        "Red" -> "Stop"
        else -> "Malfunction"
    }

    println(trafficAction)  
    // Stop
}
```

