TITLE: Defining Input Reading Helper Functions in Kotlin 1.6+
DESCRIPTION: Provides a set of private helper functions for simplifying input reading in competitive programming using Kotlin 1.6+. Functions include `readStr` for reading a single string line, `readInt` for a single integer, `readStrings` for a list of strings split by spaces, and `readInts` for a list of integers. These helpers utilize `readln()`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/competitive-programming.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
private fun readStr() = readln() // string line
private fun readInt() = readStr().toInt() // single int
private fun readStrings() = readStr().split(" ") // list of strings
private fun readInts() = readStrings().map { it.toInt() } // list of ints
```

