TITLE: Using Lateinit with Top-level Properties and Local Variables in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the lateinit modifier with local variables, which was introduced in Kotlin 1.2. It creates a cycle of three nodes where one node references another that hasn't been defined yet.
