TITLE: Implementing Function f Functionally with Tail Recursion in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Defines the function `f(x)` required by the "Reachable Numbers" problem. It first adds 1 to `x` and then recursively removes trailing zeros using a helper tail-recursive function `removeZeroes`. This demonstrates a functional approach in Kotlin.
