TITLE: When Expression with Else If and Guard Condition Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates using `else if` with a guard condition inside a `when` expression. This example combines type checking with boolean conditions, providing more flexible control flow. It uses `animal.eatsPlants` as a condition in the `else if` block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/control-flow.md#_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
when (animal) {
    // Checks if `animal` is `Dog`
    is Animal.Dog -> feedDog()
    // Guard condition that checks if `animal` is `Cat` and not `mouseHunter`
    is Animal.Cat if !animal.mouseHunter -> feedCat()
    // Calls giveLettuce() if none of the above conditions match and animal.eatsPlants is true
    else if animal.eatsPlants -> giveLettuce()
    // Prints "Unknown animal" if none of the above conditions match
    else -> println("Unknown animal")
}
```

