TITLE: Kotlin Multiplatform Source Set Access (Kotlin)
DESCRIPTION: This Kotlin code demonstrates accessing source sets in a Kotlin Multiplatform project using the new static accessors introduced in Kotlin 2.0.20.  It shows how to configure language settings for `commonMain` and access platform-specific source sets like `jvmMain`, `linuxX64Main`, and `linuxArm64Main`.  It also highlights the warning issued when accessing a source set without declaring the corresponding target.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/whatsnew/whatsnew2020.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
kotlin {
    jvm()
    linuxX64()
    linuxArm64()
    mingwX64()

    sourceSets {
        commonMain.languageSettings {
            progressiveMode = true
        }


        jvmMain { }
        linuxX64Main { }
        linuxArm64Main { }
        // Warning: accessing source set without registering the target
        iosX64Main { }
    }
}
```

