TITLE: Temporarily Allowing Exposure of Private Nested Types from Private-in-File Types (Kotlin)
DESCRIPTION: This Kotlin compiler flag disables the error introduced in Kotlin 1.6 that prohibits exposing private nested types and inner classes from types marked as private-in-file. It allows temporarily reverting to the pre-1.6 behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/compatibility-guides/compatibility-guide-16.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
-XXLanguage:-PrivateInFileEffectiveVisibility
```

