TITLE: Iterating Over a Range in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates various ways to iterate over a range in Kotlin. It showcases closed-ended ranges (inclusive), open-ended ranges (exclusive), stepping, counting down, and using `forEach`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jetbrains/kotlin-web-site/blob/master/docs/topics/idioms.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
for (i in 1..100) { ... }  // closed-ended range: includes 100
for (i in 1..<100) { ... } // open-ended range: does not include 100
for (x in 2..10 step 2) { ... }
for (x in 10 downTo 1) { ... }
(1..10).forEach { ... }
```

